cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.SY

This paper is about a mobile communication scheme that uses reinforcement learning to address jamming and interference. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also extensively uses machine learning techniques, specifically deep Q-network and convolutional neural network, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with security issues related to jamming, which could place it in cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the use of reinforcement learning in a dynamic game framework could also make it relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
